Bloco Duração Atividades / Conteúdo 2.1 Warm‑up &amp; revisão de Keyframes 30 min - Mini‑quiz rápido (5 perguntas) sobre sintaxe de <code>@keyframes</code>, propriedades <code>animation-*</code>. - Revisão ao vivo de um exemplo clássico (fade‑in + slide‑up). 2.2 Conceitos de Scroll‑Based Animation 45 min - Por que animar no scroll? Impacto na UX (guia visual, storytelling). - Diferença entre time‑driven e position‑driven animations. - Demonstrações: sites que usam scroll para revelar conteúdo (Apple, Awwwards). 2.3 API nativa – IntersectionObserver 45 min - Sintaxe básica (<code>new IntersectionObserver(callback, options)</code>). - Opções importantes: <code>rootMargin</code>, <code>threshold</code>. - Laboratório: criar um “reveal on scroll” usando apenas CSS + JS vanilla. 2.4 Pausa &amp; Perguntas 15 min Café, dúvidas rápidas. 2.5 Bibliotecas leves – AOS / ScrollReveal 40 min - Instalação via CDN. - Configurações globais (offset, duration, easing). - Exercício: aplicar três efeitos diferentes (fade‑right, zoom‑in, flip‑up) em uma landing page de exemplo. 2.6 Parallax simples com CSS &amp; transform 30 min - <code>position: sticky</code> + <code>transform: translateY(var(--scroll))</code>. - Demo: camada de fundo que se move mais lentamente que o conteúdo frontal. 2.7 GSAP + ScrollTrigger (avançado) 55 min - Importar GSAP + ScrollTrigger via CDN. - Criar uma timeline que controla múltiplas animações simultâneas (texto, imagem, background). - Uso de <code>scrub</code>, <code>pin</code>, <code>markers</code> para depuração. - Exercício guiado: hero section com sequência de animações que avança conforme o usuário rola. 2.8 Performance &amp; Acessibilidade 20 min - <code>will-change</code>, <code>translateZ(0)</code>. - Throttle/Debounce manual vs. <code>requestAnimationFrame</code>. - Respeitar <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> – fallback CSS. 2.9 Projeto rápido – “One‑Page Story” 30 min Em duplas, montar uma página de 4‑5 seções que: 1️⃣ Revela texto ao entrar na viewport. 2️⃣ Usa parallax de fundo. 3️⃣ Tem um botão “voltar ao topo” animado. Entrega: link para CodePen/JSFiddle. 2.10 Wrap‑up &amp; próximos passos 10 min Recapitular pontos críticos, indicar leituras adicionais, abrir espaço para dúvidas finais. <p>Total ≈ 4 h (inclui pausa).</p> <p>2.3 Scroll Animation using IntersectionObserver</p> <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body { margin: 0; font-family: Arial; }
        .spacer { height: 100vh; background: #f0f0f0; }
        .target {
            width: 300px;
            height: 300px;
            background: #667eea;
            margin: 50px auto;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: white;
            font-size: 18px;
            opacity: 0.3;
            transform: scale(0.8);
            transition: all 0.6s ease;
        }
        .target.visible {
            opacity: 1;
            transform: scale(1);
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="spacer"&gt;Role para baixo&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="target"&gt;Elemento 1&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="target"&gt;Elemento 2&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="target"&gt;Elemento 3&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;script&gt;
        const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) =&gt; {
            entries.forEach(entry =&gt; {
                if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                    entry.target.classList.add('visible');
                } else {
                    entry.target.classList.remove('visible');
                }
            });
        }, {
            threshold: 0.5 // 50% do elemento deve estar visível
        });

        // Observar todos os elementos .target
        document.querySelectorAll('.target').forEach(target =&gt; {
            observer.observe(target);
        });
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre> <p>2.3 Scroll Animation para uma barra de progresso</p> <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body { 
            margin: 0; 
            font-family: Arial;
            height: 300vh; /* conteúdo longo para scroll */
        }

        .progress-bar {
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            height: 4px;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #667eea, #764ba2);
            width: 0%;
            transition: width 0.1s ease;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .content {
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .section {
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 2em;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="progress-bar"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="content"&gt;
        &lt;div class="section"&gt;Secção 1&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="section"&gt;Secção 2&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="section"&gt;Secção 3&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;script&gt;
        const progressBar = document.querySelector('.progress-bar');

        // Throttle para performance
        let ticking = false;

        function updateProgressBar() {
            const scrollTop = window.pageYOffset;
            const docHeight = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
            const scrollPercent = (scrollTop / docHeight) * 100;

            progressBar.style.width = scrollPercent + '%';
            ticking = false;
        }

        window.addEventListener('scroll', () =&gt; {
            if (!ticking) {
                requestAnimationFrame(updateProgressBar);
                ticking = true;
            }
        });
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre> <p>2.3 Exemplo de animações simultâneas com delay sequenciais desencadeados pela scroll. Exemplo com 4 cartões</p> <p>[!NOTE] Title Contents</p> <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body { margin: 0; padding: 20px; font-family: Arial; }

        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 100px 0;
        }

        .card {
            width: 300px;
            height: 200px;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            margin: 50px;
            display: inline-block;
            opacity: 0;
            transform: translateY(0px);
            transition: all 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94);
        }

        .card.animate {
            opacity: 1;
            transform: translateY(60px) rotate(10deg);
        }

        /* Delays escalonados */
        .card:nth-child(1).animate { transition-delay: 0.1s; }
        .card:nth-child(2).animate { transition-delay: 0.5s; }
        .card:nth-child(3).animate { transition-delay: 1s; }
        .card:nth-child(4).animate { transition-delay: 1.4s; }

        .spacer { height: 100vh; }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="spacer"&gt;Role para baixo&lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="container"&gt;
        &lt;div class="card"&gt;Card 1&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="card"&gt;Card 2&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="card"&gt;Card 3&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="card"&gt;Card 4&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;script&gt;
        const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) =&gt; {
            entries.forEach(entry =&gt; {
                if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                    // Animar todos os cards do container
                    const cards = entry.target.querySelectorAll('.card');
                    cards.forEach(card =&gt; card.classList.add('animate'));
                }
            });
        }, { threshold: 0.2 });

        observer.observe(document.querySelector('.container'));
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre> <p>2.3 Exemplo de rotação com base em scroll</p> <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body { 
            margin: 0; 
            font-family: Arial;
            height: 400vh;
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #667eea, #764ba2);
        }

        .rotating-element {
            position: fixed;
            top: 50%;
            left: 50%;
            width: 200px;
            height: 200px;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
            will-change: transform;
        }

        .scroll-indicator {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 50px;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            color: white;
            font-size: 18px;
            text-align: center;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="rotating-element"&gt;
        Role a página
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="scroll-indicator"&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;Progresso: &lt;span id="progress"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;%&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;Rotação: &lt;span id="rotation"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;°&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;script&gt;
        const rotatingElement = document.querySelector('.rotating-element');
        const progressSpan = document.getElementById('progress');
        const rotationSpan = document.getElementById('rotation');

        function updateRotation() {
            const scrollTop = window.pageYOffset;
            const docHeight = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
            const scrollFraction = scrollTop / docHeight;

            // Rotação completa (360°) ao chegar ao fim
            const rotation = scrollFraction * 360;

            // Escala baseada no scroll (0.5x a 1.5x)
            const scale = 0.5 + (scrollFraction * 1);

            rotatingElement.style.transform = 
                `translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(${rotation}deg) scale(${scale})`;

            // Atualizar indicadores
            progressSpan.textContent = Math.round(scrollFraction * 100);
            rotationSpan.textContent = Math.round(rotation);
            ticking = false;
        }

        let ticking = false;
        window.addEventListener('scroll', () =&gt; {
            if (!ticking) {
                requestAnimationFrame(updateRotation);
                ticking = true;
            }
        });
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre> <p>2.6 Parallax</p> <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body { margin: 0; font-family: Arial; }


        /* Método alternativo com JavaScript */
        .hero {
            height: 100vh;
            background: url('data:image/svg+xml,&lt;svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 100 100"&gt;&lt;circle cx="20" cy="20" r="2" fill="%23fff" opacity="0.3"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="80" cy="40" r="1" fill="%23fff" opacity="0.5"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="40" cy="80" r="1.5" fill="%23fff" opacity="0.4"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;') #667eea;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: white;
            font-size: 3em;
            position: relative;

        }

        .content {
            background: white;
            min-height: 200vh;
            padding: 50px;
            position: relative;
            z-index: 1;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="hero"&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;Scroll Parallax&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="content"&gt;
        &lt;h2&gt;Conteúdo Principal&lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit...&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;script&gt;
        const hero = document.querySelector('.hero');

        function updateParallax() {
            const scrolled = window.pageYOffset;
            const parallax = scrolled * 0.5;

            hero.style.transform = `translateY(${parallax}px)`;
            ticking = false;
        }

        let ticking = false;
        window.addEventListener('scroll', () =&gt; {
            if (!ticking) {
                requestAnimationFrame(updateParallax);
                ticking = true;
            }
        });
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>
